facts.fact_text: The unemployment rate in the Philippines remained at 4.4% in December 2025, unchanged from November.

evidences.evidence_text: The unemployment rate in the Philippines remained at 4.4% in December 2025, unchanged from November, reflecting stable labor market conditions.

facts.fact_text: The unemployment rate in December 2025 was higher than the 3.1% recorded in December 2024.

evidences.evidence_text: However, it was higher than the 3.1% recorded in December 2024.

facts.fact_text: The number of unemployed persons rose slightly to 2.26 million in December 2025 from 2.25 million in November and 1.63 million a year earlier.

evidences.evidence_text: The number of unemployed persons rose slightly to 2.26 million from 2.25 million in November and 1.63 million a year earlier.

facts.fact_text: Total employment in the Philippines increased to 49.43 million in December 2025 from 49.26 million in November but remained below December 2024’s 50.19 million.

evidences.evidence_text: Total employment increased to 49.43 million from 49.26 million in November but remained below December 2024’s 50.19 million.

facts.fact_text: Services continued to dominate employment at 62.4% of total workers, followed by agriculture at 20.7% and industry at 16.9%.

evidences.evidence_text: Among major sectors, services continued to dominate employment at 62.4% of total workers, followed by agriculture at 20.7% and industry at 16.9%.

facts.fact_text: The labor force participation rate was 64.4% in December 2025, up from 64.0% in November but below December 2024’s 65.1%.
